# Linux common commands example

List common commands example of linux for fast reference

df - report file system disk space usage

usage:
df

find -

grep -

ls -

ps -


- [tail] -

tail - output the last part of files

usage:

tail [FILE]
tail -f [FILE]

  - the second example uses -f option to keep monitor the file. (useful for monitor log)

- [tar] -

tar

tar -zcvf xxx.tar.gz /path


